result.name: Ginza Okura Japanese Restaurant

reviews.text: This place is not cheap but food is very good. Many customers are Japanese - a good sign of authenticity! I came here for team gathering because my boss (Japanese) decided this place. We got 6-7tables. It turned out to be a super fun night and everyone enjoyed themselves, including my other Japanese colleague who end up going out with the random Japanese guys by sushi bar drinking another round. Months later another friend of mine also happened to recommend this place to me as a good lunch option - apparently their lunch menu is much cheaper. I would come back for a date night.
Traditional Japanese resturant food is good quality and service is good.less this kind of resturant in the market
The sushi box set is very tasty and you feel enough and full after finish this. The environment is silent for you to enough your meat.

since i am vegan, i couldn't enjoy most of the food there including the omakase by the chef. However they still had some veggie options such as the cucumber rolls, tempura and steamed veggies with various pickled veggies
Great sashimi & fish. Authentic Japanese. Bit pricy so perfect for special occasions. I would defo recommend to people and would go back again. Staff very nice.

食物水準一般，價格不便宜，地方錯
